Allowable setback encroachments summary

**Main dwelling**
*   **Feature**: 1st floor portion at rear of structure ≤ half width of structure
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: to within 14' of rear lot line
    *   **Code Sec**: 18.12.050 (a)(2)
    *   **Illustration**: Fig 18 on this page
*   **Feature**: 1st floor extension of an existing front setback encroachment
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: to within 14' of front lot line
    *   **Code Sec**: 18.12.050 (a)(1)(A)
    *   **Illustration**: Fig 19 p. 25
*   **Feature**: 1st floor extension of an existing interior-side setback encroachment
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: to within 5' of interior-side lot line
    *   **Code Sec**: 18.12.050 (a)(1)(B)
    *   **Illustration**: Fig 19 p. 25
*   **Feature**: 1st floor extension of an existing street-side setback encroachment
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: to within 10' of street-side lot line
    *   **Code Sec**: 18.12.050 (a)(1)(C)
    *   **Illustration**: Fig 19 p. 25
*   **Feature**: Attached storage closets ≤ 6' in height & ≤ 25 sf
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: 4' into front & rear yards & 2' into side yards

**Detached accessory structures**
*   **Feature**: that are 75' from front lot line and 20' from street-side lot line
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: in rear or side yards
    *   **Code Sec**: 18.12.080 (b)(3)
    *   **Illustration**: Fig 34 p. 39
*   **Feature**: that are for covered parking and on lots ≤ 95' deep and 25' from street-side lot line and in rear half of lot
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: in rear or side yards

**Porches and entry features**
*   **Feature**: 1st floor balconies, uncovered porches, stairways, and fire escapes
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: 6' into front & rear yard & 3' into the side yards
    *   **Code Sec**: 18.12.050 (a)(3)(D)
*   **Feature**: 1st floor only canopies & patio covers
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: rear or side yards
    *   **Code Sec**: 18.12.050 (a)(3)(E)

**Other**
*   **Feature**: Eaves & cornices
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: 2' into side & 4' into front & rear yards
    *   **Code Sec**: 18.12.050 (a)(3)(A)
*   **Feature**: 1st floor bay / greenhouse windows composed of a window surface & cantilevered with no floor joists.
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: 2' into front yard & 3' into rear yard
    *   **Code Sec**: 18.12.050 (a)(3)(B)
*   **Feature**: Greenhouse windows only
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: 2' into side yards
*   **Feature**: Uncovered parking
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: in rear or side yards except for 1st 10' of street side yard to within 6' of rear & interior-side lot lines
    *   **Code Sec**: 18.12.060 (.c)
    *   **Illustration**: Fig 34 p. 39
*   **Feature**: Pools & spas (not equipment)
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: 2' into side yard
*   **Feature**: Fireplaces ≤ 5' wide

**Excavated features**
*   **Feature**: Lightwells and stairwells (cumulative length ≤ 15')
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: 3' into side yards & 4' into rear yard
    *   **Code Sec**: 18.12.090 (c)
    *   **Illustration**: Fig 39 p. 42
*   **Feature**: Below grade patios (cumulative length ≤ 5')
    *   **Allowable encroachment**: 2' into side yards & 4' into rear yard
    *   **Illustration**: Fig 40 p. 43

**Allowable rear encroachment**
**Fig 18 Allowable encroachment: rear yard**

**Rear yard encroachment**
A portion of the main dwelling (no wider than half the max. width of the dwelling), may encroach into the rear setback, at the ground floor only, as follows:
*   For all lots except back-to-back corner lots, up to 6', providing a minimum setback of 14' is maintained.
*   For back-to-back corner lots, up to 10', providing a minimum setback of 10' is maintained.

**Note:**
*   Multiple protrusions are not permitted; addition must be contiguous with existing protrusion.
*   Only for legally constructed structures (no variance or an home-improvement exception (HIE)).
*   Only once in the life of the structure.

*   **1st story Addition**

*   **New OR Existing main dwelling**
*   **Buildable area**
*   **Front yard**
*   **Interior-side yard**
*   **Setback that is to be maintained per notes above**
*   **Allowable rear yard encroachment per notes above**
